# Project Documentation – Art History Explorer

## 1. Project Overview

Art History Explorer is a frontend web application designed to showcase famous artworks with an interactive and modern UI.

---

## 2. Architecture

Frontend Only Application:

- HTML → Structure
- CSS → Styling & Layout
- JavaScript → Interactivity

No backend used.

---

## 3. Core Components

### Navbar
Sticky glass effect navigation.

### Hero Section
Gradient-based startup-style landing section.

### Gallery Section
Grid-based artwork display.

### Filter System
Uses class-based filtering.

### Search Feature
JavaScript text matching via DOM.

### Modal System
Dynamic content injection using JS.

---

## 4. Performance Optimization

- Optimized image sizing
- Responsive grid layout
- Lightweight vanilla JS

---

## 5. Challenges Faced

- Broken image links
- UI responsiveness
- Filter + Search interaction logic

---

## 6. Future Scope

- Backend integration
- User accounts
- Artwork database
- API integration (Met Museum API)
